(192, 1, '2014-01-30 15:36:32', '2014-01-30 15:36:32', '<!--:en--><h2>Reaching the Hardest to Reach Children</h2>\r\n<h1 style=\"color:blue; font-weight:bold;\">SHARE Education Programme Bangladesh</h1>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.sajibbiswas.com/shareeducation/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/01.jpg\"><img src=\"http://www.sajibbiswas.com/shareeducation/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/01-158x300.jpg\" alt=\"01\" width=\"158\" height=\"300\" class=\"alignnone size-medium wp-image-188\" /></a>\r\n<p>The SHARE education programme is co-financed by the European Union for about 490 crore taka. It aims to provide primary education to 655,460 hard to reach children of Bangladesh from 2012 to 2017. SHARE is made up of four projects, namely Aloghar (Lighthouse), SHIKHON (Learning) II, SUSTAIN and UNIQUE II.  The programme is complemented by a coordination unit managed by a consortium led by Human Dynamics, Austria. It ensures exchange of information, lessons learned and knowledge management of the programme. </p><!--:-->', '<!--:en-->Overview<!--:--><!--:bn-->সাধারণভাবে 	<!--:-->', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '40-revision-v1', '', '', '2014-01-30 15:36:32', '2014-01-30 15:36:32', '', 40, 'http://www.sajibbiswas.com/shareeducation/40-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
