(288, 1, '2014-02-02 16:49:25', '2014-02-02 16:49:25', '<!--:en--><a href=\"http://www.sajibbiswas.com/shareeducation/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/1.png\"><img src=\"http://www.sajibbiswas.com/shareeducation/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/1.png\" alt=\"1\" width=\"700\" height=\"56\" class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-283\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<h1 style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Overview of the SHARE Programme </h1>\r\n\r\n<p>The SHARE (supporting the hardest to reach through basic education) programme is designed to bring basic education to the hardest to reach children in Bangladesh. SHARE is concerned to bring excellence in education to some of the poorest children in Bangladesh and to support the development of quality basic education through the dissemination of information and the testing out of practical models. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The overall objective of the SHARE programme is: \r\nto contribute to the achievement of Bangladesh’s development goals and to a national basic education framework.</p>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.sajibbiswas.com/shareeducation/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/2.png\"><img src=\"http://www.sajibbiswas.com/shareeducation/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/2.png\" alt=\"2\" width=\"252\" height=\"500\" class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-284\" /></a>\r\n<p>SHARE has two Components. SHARE Component I is made up of four programmes: Caritas Bangladesh is implementing a project called ‘Aloghar’ (Lighthouse), Dhaka Ahsania Mission is implementing ‘Unique intervention for quality primary education -UNIQUE II’, Save the Children Bangladesh is implementing ‘SHIKHON ( Learning) II’ and ‘Support Urban Slum Children to Access Inclusive Non-Formal Education -SUSTAIN’. With a total of 49 million Euros of EU funding between them, these projects are bringing basic education to at least 650,000 children in Bangladesh who, because they have dropped out of formal school, are geographically remote, speak a home language other than Bangla, have some disability or are working or street children, do not access mainstream education.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>SHARE Component II works with Component I to support knowledge management, capacity building and coordination within the overall SHARE programme and is designed to learn and disseminate lessons about what works best and why, to share best practice, and to help build results-based-management capacity and culture, as well as facilitating linkages with the formal primary education system and other Non - Formal Education initiatives. Human Dynamics is a European TA firm selected by EU to implement Component II of the SHARE programme. Component II promotes the sharing of expertise between those working for the four SHARE partner projects and the Sharing Seminars are designed to support that sharing.</p>\r\n\r\n<h1 style=\"font-weight:bold;\">Overview of the two SHARE Sharing Seminars</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>This document reports on the first of two Sharing Seminars held in November 2013 in Dinajpur and Savar. At the request of the partners the participants are largely supervisors and teacher trainers. Instead of the four sessions predicted in the Inception Report. two Sharing Seminars were implemented in the first year, to allow interaction between SHARE NGO partners’ staff of similar level. Both programmes took place over two and a half days, some participants travelling long distances to attend the programmes. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The facilitator of both programmes was Ms Manjusree Mitra supported by Valerie Emblen. The language was Bangla.The programme is to be found in Annex One. The facilitators were impressed by the knowledge and commitment of the participants. Their willingness to exchange and explore ideas was noted, with a lack of competitiveness or desire to promote the supremacy of any particular approach. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>A full list of participants is to be found Annex 2. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Participants at the Dinajpur Sharing Seminar </p>\r\n\r\n<p> 41 participants from SHARE partners and their implementing partners took part, from the eastern part of Bangladesh. A full list of participants is to be found Annex 2. Ms Laila Baqee, Education Advisor, EUD, spent the whole of the time with the programme. </p>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.sajibbiswas.com/shareeducation/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/3.png\"><img src=\"http://www.sajibbiswas.com/shareeducation/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/3.png\" alt=\"3\" width=\"635\" height=\"385\" class=\"alignright size-full wp-image-285\" /></a>\r\nbusy. However, we hope that their accepting of the invitation suggests that cooperation is possible in the future.\r\n\r\nThe number of participants from implementing organisations is recorded below:\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.sajibbiswas.com/shareeducation/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/41.png\"><img src=\"http://www.sajibbiswas.com/shareeducation/wp-content/uploads/2014/01/41.png\" alt=\"4\" width=\"244\" height=\"128\" class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-286\" /></a>\r\n\r\n<!--:--><!--:bn-->ত্বে আ ফ ম রুহুল হক থাকার সময় এর অধিকাংশকে দলীয় বিবেচনায় অনুমোদন দেয়া হয় বলে অভিযোগ রয়েছে।স্বাস্থ্যমন্ত্রীর দায়িত্বে আ ফ ম রুহুল হক থাকার সময় এর অধিকাংশকে দলীয় বিবেচনায় অনুমোদন দেয়া হয় বলে অভিযোগ রয়েছে।স্বাস্থ্যমন্ত্রীর দায়িত্বে আ ফ ম রুহুল হক থাকার সময় এর অধিকাংশকে দলীয় বিবেচনায় অনুমোদন দেয়া হয় বলে অভিযোগ রয়েছে।স্বাস্থ্যমন্ত্রীর দায়িত্বে আ ফ ম রুহুল হক থাকার সময় এর অধিকাংশকে দলীয় বিবেচনায় অনুমোদন দেয়া হয় বলে অভিযোগ রয়েছে।স্বাস্থ্যমন্ত্রীর দায়িত্বে আ ফ ম রুহুল হক থাকার সময় এর অধিকাংশকে দলীয় বিবেচনায় অনুমোদন দেয়া হয় বলে অভিযোগ রয়েছে।স্বাস্থ্যমন্ত্রীর দায়িত্বে আ ফ ম রুহুল হক থাকার সময় এর অধিকাংশকে দলীয় বিবেচনায় অনুমোদন দেয়া হয় বলে অভিযোগ রয়েছে।স্বাস্থ্যমন্ত্রীর দায়িত্বে আ ফ ম রুহুল হক থাকার সময় এর অধিকাংশকে দলীয় বিবেচনায় অনুমোদন দেয়া হয় বলে অভিযোগ রয়েছে।স্বাস্থ্যমন্ত্রীর দায়িত্বে আ ফ ম রুহুল হক থাকার সময় এর অধিকাংশকে দলীয় বিবেচনায় অনুমোদন দেয়া হয় বলে অভিযোগ রয়েছে।স্বাস্থ্যমন্ত্রীর দায়িত্বে আ ফ ম রুহুল হক থাকার সময় এর অধিকাংশকে দলীয় বিবেচনায় অনুমোদন দেয়া হয় বলে অভিযোগ রয়েছে।স্বাস্থ্যমন্ত্রীর দায়িত্বে আ ফ ম রুহুল হক থাকার সময় এ