(299, 1, '2014-02-02 18:17:25', '2014-02-02 18:17:25', '<!--:en-->SUSTAIN - Support Urban Slum Children to Access Inclusive Non-formal education\r\nObjectives\r\nOverall Objective: To increase equal access to quality basic education in a safe learning environment for hardest to reach children in urban slums of Dhaka and Chittagong and mainstream students into the formal education system or into other educational alternatives.\r\nSpecific Objective 1: Increased access to and completion of child-friendly pre-primary (PPE) and non-formal primary education (NFPE) has been achieved for hardest to reach urban working children or those at risk of becoming working children.\r\nSpecific Objective 2: Increased opportunities for the hardest to reach working children or those at risk of becoming working children in urban areas for continuing their formal or non-formal education beyond the provision of basic education.\r\nSpecific Objective 3: Improved inclusiveness and quality of the primary education provision.\r\nKey Results\r\n	8,000 children at risk have successfully completed1-year PPE\r\n	30,888 out of school working children condensed NFPE course\r\n	English-based NFPE curriculum has been successfully introduced\r\n	20,000 guardians have received parenting education\r\n	13,406 are enrolled in formal schools to continue their education\r\n	Children who cannot enroll into formal schools, are linked to alternative education opportunities\r\n	Access to education for hardest to reach children improved through child-led advocacy\r\n	GoB is actively engaged in a dialogue to review the competency needs\r\n	Participatory monitoring system on NFPE quality is in place and applied by the CMC members in the project area.\r\nTarget Groups\r\n	38,988 urban working children\r\n	17,500 parents and 2,500 employers of the children,\r\n	76,800 formal school students,\r\n	192 SMCs and 960 teachers from formal schools,\r\n	400 local government/ward officials,\r\n	50 state officials from MOPME and NCTB\r\n	250 representatives from primary education and NFPE providing organizations/institutions\r\nContract\r\nRef. DCI-ASIE/2011/262-810\r\nDuration\r\nDecember 2011 – December 2017\r\nLocation\r\nDhaka City Corporation: 17 wards \r\nChittagong City Corporation: 15 wards\r\nBudget\r\nTotal budget: EURO 5,273,439\r\nCurrent year budget: EURO 951,208\r\nContributions\r\nEU: EURO 5,009,767 (95%)\r\nSC: EURO 263,672 (5%)\r\nPartners\r\nNari Maitree (NM)\r\nSociety for Underprivileged Families (SUF)\r\nSocial and Economic Enhancement Program (SEEP)\r\nUnderprivileged Children’s Educational Program (UCEP)\r\nOrganization for Women Development in Bangladesh (OWDEB)\r\nProject Design\r\n	The project activities take place in physical structures based on a compound system.\r\n	To cover all targeted 30888 NFPE students, 39 compound building will be rented.\r\n	Within 39 compounds, 27 will include 1 PPE centre each to cover the targeted 8100 PPE students.\r\n	Each of the 39 compounds will cover 4 NFPE centers and 1 child club.\r\n	Each PPE, NFPE centre and child club will have 1 room within the compounds.\r\n	PPE centers each room will accommodate two (2) classes/shifts with 25 students each.\r\n	NFPE centers each room will accommodate three (3) classes/shifts with 30 students each.\r\n	In project areas where the necessary building infrastructure is not available, a catchment area of around two square kilometers in average is considered to accommodate the compounds. The setup will ensure short distance for the PPE and NFPE students to attend the centers and co-curricular activities in the child clubs and it reduces the number of child clubs and CMCs needed, which contributes to a cost efficient project setup.\r\n	The description refers to 39 compounds/catchment areas, with 156 NFPE centers (4 centers per compound/catchment areax39) and 27 PPE centers and 39 child clubs and 39 CMCs.\r\nMain Activities\r\n	Provision of PPE and NFPE\r\n	Piloting of English based NFPE curriculum\r\n	Child clubs\r\n	Parenting education for guardians\r\n	Sensitisation of stakeholders on constraints of working children\r\n	Tutorial support for graduated students to access formal school system\r\n	Local level child-led advocacy\r\n	Advocacy with GoB to review the requirements for grade 5 examinations\r\n	Development of a comprehensive monitoring guideline for learning centres\r\n	Documentation of best practices\r\nProgress ( January to May  2012)\r\n	Staff recruitment: Staff recruitment of both Save the Children (SC) and 5 partners has been completed by this time. Total staff recruited 388.\r\n	Student Survey: Student survey for enrollment of PPE and NFE has been completed.\r\n	Student Enrollment: 1350 PPE and 14040 NFPE students enrolled.\r\n	Set up Compound: All 39 compounds including 1 PPE, 4 NFPE and 1 Child Club have been established.\r\n	Communication and Visibility plan: The communication and Visibility plan has been approved by EU.\r\n	Steering Committee (PMSC): Project steering committee has been formed. ToR for the steering committee has been finalized.\r\n	Procurement of Centre Logistics: All school materials for 39 compounds have been procured.\r\n	Procurement of Education Materials: All learning materials for 1350 PPE students and 14040 NFPE students have been procured.\r\n	Basic Training for PPE and NFPE teachers: 9 batches of Basic training for PPE and NFPE teachers have been completed.\r\n	Provision of Information Box: All 183 centers established information box.\r\n	Baseline Survey: Baseline survey for SUSTAIN project is going on in 38 wards.\r\nNext Highlights Activities (June to August 2012)\r\n	Completion of Baseline Survey in 38 wards of Dhaka and Chittagong City Corporation.\r\n	Publication of Communication, Visibility and Behavioral Change and Communication (BCC) materials and distribute to relevant stakeholders.\r\n	Organize workshop on Review and Condensing of English Curriculum.\r\