(670, 1, '2015-06-14 04:31:17', '2015-06-14 04:31:17', '<!--:en--><strong> </strong>\r\n<h1>Technical Assistance</h1>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\nThe mid-term review of SHARE\'s predecessor NFPE programme highlighted that the exchange of information and best practice among the NGOs in the network as well as with the government and other civil society actors is an important ingredient of success. Knowledge management, capacity building and coordination have consequently been scaled up and streamlined; and they have become the core of one of the two components of the SHARE programme. Thus, Technical Assistance (TA) is concerned with knowledge management, capacity building, coordination, policy dialogue and synthesis of lessons learned. As a discrete component located within the overall SHARE programme TA is specifically designed to yield lessons about what works best and why, to share best practice, and to help build results-based-management capacity and culture, in coherent linkages with the formal primary education system and other NFE initiatives. TA has a duration of 78 months, starting on Jan 25th 2012 and ending on 24th July 2018.\r\nThe overall objective for SHARE TA component is the same as that of four SHARE projects, that is: to contribute to the achievement of Bangladesh’s development goals and to a national basic education framework.\r\n<strong>\r\n</strong>\r\n<h3>The TA of the SHARE programme has four main thrusts:</h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\n1. sharing experience among SHARE partner NGOs, with the NGO community at large and with Government;\r\n2. extending and disseminating information produced by SHARE;\r\n3. supporting the development of current practice in education;\r\n4. supporting NGOs to improve their effectiveness, further define their roles and to forge stronger links with Government.\r\n5. A particular work of component II is setting up of an interactive web site. It will be in action by the end of the first year of implementation and will host documents created through the project and the programme’s database.\r\nTA addresses Results Three and Four of the SHARE education programme.\r\n<strong>\r\n</strong>\r\n<h3>Result Three is:</h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\nlessons learned, best practices and materials shared and disseminated, and used in the NGO community and, if desired by government, responsible government agencies to inform policy and practice.\r\n<strong>\r\n</strong>\r\n<h3>Result Four is:</h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<strong></strong>\r\nresults-based management institutionalised by NGOs and, if desired by government, at relevant government institutions.\r\nThis Component is implementing by a consortium led by Human Dynamics, Austria. Consortium members are Centre for British Teachers (CfBT Education Trust), UK; The Institute of Governance Studies (IGS), BRAC, Bangladesh; and CARE Osterreich, Austria.\r\n<div id=\"__if72ru4sdfsdfrkjahiuyi_once\" style=\"display: none;\"></div>\r\n<div id=\"__zsc_once\"></div>\r\n<div id=\"__hggasdgjhsagd_once\" style=\"display: none;\"></div><!--:-->', '<!--:en-->Technical Assistance<!--:-->', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '162-revision-v1', '', '', '2015-06-14 04:31:17', '2015-06-14 04:31:17', '', 162, 'http://share-education.org/162-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
