(972, 1, '2017-09-17 09:12:32', '2017-09-17 09:12:32', 'During 2015 the SHARE education program had continued to build on as well as consolidate its achievements and good practices in primary education. It maintained an impressive drive to enrol and retain children in SHARE schools in some of the hardest to reach locations in the country and most of the children who completed grade V passed the National PECE examinations held in December 2015 and progressed to secondary level of education in formal schools.\r\n\r\nThe mid-term review (MTR) conducted by independent team of consultants concluded that SHARE had achieved remarkable success thus far and was poised to accomplish or even exceed all the set targets of access and quality in providing basic education to the children of the poor, impoverished and ethnic communities living in remote and hard to reach areas of Bangladesh who are mostly outside the radar of public services.\r\n\r\nDuring the year SHARE also continued to address the cross-cutting themes including mainstreaming children into the formal school system, building strong community relations and a sense of ownership by the community. These efforts will continue to be strengthened and consolidated for the remainder of the project period.', '‍Annual Report 2015', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', '%e2%80%8dannual-report-2015', '', '', '2017-09-17 09:24:39', '2017-09-17 09:24:39', '', 0, 'http://share-education.org/?post_type=knowledgecentre&#038;p=972', 0, 'knowledgecentre', '', 0),
